HEADWORD: Coquille
<hw>Co*quille"</hw> <pr>(k⟦osl⟧*k⟦emac⟧l"; <it>F.</it>
k⟦osl⟧`k⟦emac⟧"y')</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[F.]</ety> <def>Lit., a
shell;</def> <specif>hence:</specif> <sd>(a)</sd> <def>A shell or
shell-like dish or mold in which viands are served.</def> <sd>(b)</sd>
<def>The expansion of the guard of a sword, dagger, etc.</def>
<sd>(c)</sd> <def>A form of ruching used as a dress trimming or for
neckwear, and named from the manner in which it is gathered or
fulled.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>Webster 1913 Suppl.</source>]</p>

